        "We're about to repair cracks in a concrete water tank. The tank holds potable water. What repair materials are appropriate?",
        "For potable water tanks, all repair materials must comply with NSF/ANSI 61 (Drinking Water System Components) certification. Appropriate materials include: NSF 61-certified structural epoxy injection for dormant cracks needing strength restoration, NSF 61-certified polyurethane injection grout for active water-bearing cracks, crystalline waterproofing admixture coatings (most major brands have NSF 61 certification) which are excellent for water tanks because they self-heal future micro-cracks, and NSF 61-certified cementitious repair mortars for spall repairs and surface preparation. Avoid silicone sealants (typically not certified for potable water contact) and standard polyurethane sealants unless specifically NSF 61 certified.",
